Subject: [PATCH] phase-5: auto promotion pipeline + calibration cron
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Activates the two governance scaffolds previously held behind `@ts-nocheck`
and wires them into the api-server lifecycle:

  - lib/governance/promotion_engine.ts — removed @ts-nocheck header,
    replaced `Math.max(severity as any, "medium")` (which silently widened
    to number) with a typed `escalateSeverity()` helper that walks a rank
    table over the literal union.

  - lib/eval/calibration_tracker.ts — removed @ts-nocheck header. Imports
    Logger from a new `lib/logging/logger.ts` shim that re-exports from
    the canonical pino logger so legacy import paths resolve without
    duplicating the pino config.

  - lib/governance/governance_scheduler.ts (NEW) — singleton that
    periodically pulls every non-retired strategy from the registry,
    maps registry state → engine tier, calls evaluatePromotion() and
    evaluateDemotion(), records the cycle in a ring buffer, and emits
    `promotion_eligible` / `demotion_signal` SSE alerts. 5 min default
    interval (GOVERNANCE_INTERVAL_MS).

  - lib/eval/calibration_scheduler.ts (NEW) — singleton that takes an
    hourly snapshot of the calibration tracker, emits a
    `calibration_snapshot` SSE event for dashboard cache invalidation
    and a `calibration_drift` SSE event whenever HIGH/CRITICAL drift
    fires. 1 hour default interval (CALIBRATION_INTERVAL_MS).

  - routes/governance_scheduler.ts (NEW) — GET status/history/current
    + POST force (operator-gated via requireOperator).

  - routes/calibration_scheduler.ts (NEW) — GET status/history/current/
    score + POST force (operator-gated).

  - index.ts — both schedulers start after server.listen() and register
    onShutdown cleanup, gated by GOVERNANCE_AUTOSTART / CALIBRATION_AUTOSTART
    (default true).

  - routes/index.ts — both new routers mounted.

